✦ For v1.6.0, we shift focus to "Intelligence & Personal Benchmarks". After solidifying SRS 2.0 in v1.5.0, we will now help users visualize their growth and speed.

  🧠 1. Smart Difficulty Analysis
   - Adaptive Goals: Automatically suggest a "Daily Goal" (e.g., 1 Hard, 2 Mediums) based on your last 7 days of performance.
   - Time-to-Solve Benchmarks: Compare your current speed against your personal average for that specific difficulty (Easy/Med/Hard) in real-time.

  📊 2. "Weak Point" Radar (Weakness Detection)
   - Tag-Based Insights: A new section in the Stats tab that identifies which topics (e.g., "Dynamic Programming", "Graphs") have the highest average solve time or lowest "Mastered" rate.
   - Topic Progress Bars: Visual indicators showing your "Mastery Level" for different LeetCode tags based on your history.

  🚀 3. Speed-Run Mode (Mock Interview Prep)
   - Session Goals: Set a goal to solve X problems in Y minutes (e.g., "Mock Contest Mode").
   - Live HUD Countdown: The floating HUD can switch from a stopwatch to a "Time Remaining" countdown for the current session.

  🌗 4. UI Polishing & Customization
   - Compact View: A "Mini-HUD" mode for the main extension that hides all tabs except the active problem timers for distraction-free work.
   - Custom Themes: Allow users to pick their own "Primary Color" (currently fixed to Green/Red).

  ---
  ✅ COMPLETED IN v1.5.0:
  - Confidence-Based Spaced Repetition (SRS 2.0).
  - Background Review Reminders & Notifications.
  - Context-Aware Icon Badge (Solved:Running+Due).
  - Environment Isolation (Red Mode) & Integrated Dev Bench.
